  <name>Twinverse</name>
  <summary>Play any game from your Steam library in splitscreen or with multiple monitors.</summary>
  <developer_name>Messias Junior</developer_name>

  <description>
    <p>
      Twinverse is an open-source tool for Linux that allows you to create and manage
      multiple instances of `gamescope` and `steam` simultaneously.
      This enables multiple players to enjoy their game library on a single computer,
      either in splitscreen mode or each with their own display, along with dedicated
      audio output and input devices.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Simple Multi-Instance Management: Run multiple Steam Client simultaneously, allowing you and your friends to enjoy your game libraries separately.</li>
      <li>Per-Instance Hardware Assignment: Assign specific mice, keyboards, and controllers to each game instance.</li>
      <li>Dedicated Audio Channels: Route audio from each game instance to a separate audio output device.</li>
      <li>Separate Home Directory: Customize settings and files for each instance individually.</li>
      <li>Shared Game Library: Share the Steam game directory among multiple instances.</li>
      <li>Use Any Proton: Use any version of Proton to run your games.</li>
      <li>Play Whatever You Want: Instances are not limited to playing the same game; each instance can play whichever game it wants.</li>
      <li>Flexible Screen Modes: Choose between splitscreen (up to 4 instances per monitor) or fullscreen (1 instance per monitor).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>How it Works:</p>
    <p>Twinverse uses Bubblewrap (bwrap), a low-level Linux sandboxing tool, to isolate each Steam Client instance. This ensures that the instances do not interfere with each other or with the user's main system. Furthermore, the Gamescope command line is dynamically generated based on the user's settings, involving the bwrap command which, in turn, launches Steam.</p>
  </description>

